# The only provider Confidant calls. No other value is currently
# registered (see src/llm/providers.py) -- an earlier automatic Ollama
# fallback was removed after the validation experiment showed it firing
# under sustained free-tier rate-limit pressure and producing severely
# degraded output at whichever stage fell back to it (see
# engine/decisions.md "Ollama removed, OpenRouter-only").
#
# CAVEAT: the interpretation grounding filters (src/interpretation/engine.py)
# were calibrated against Ollama/llama3.2:3b specifically, back when it was
# still the primary provider -- see engine/decisions.md. Running against
# OpenRouter means every turn now uses a model that hasn't been through
# that same n=10 validation.
LLM_PROVIDER=openrouter

# Generic key, used as a fallback for any provider below that doesn't have
# its own key set. Handy if you only want to manage one secret.
LLM_API_KEY=

# --- OpenRouter (https://openrouter.ai/keys) ---
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
# `openrouter/free` -- OpenRouter's own auto-router: it randomly selects
# a free model per-request from whatever's currently available, filtered
# to models that support the request's needed features (structured
# outputs, tool calling, etc.), rather than pinning to one specific free
# model that might individually be overloaded (pinning to a single free
# model has its own documented failure mode -- see engine/decisions.md --
# that specific model getting rate-limited harder than the rotating pool
# as a whole). Confirmed $0.00 cost and capabilities via OpenRouter's own
# pricing page 2026-07-05.
#
# Rate limits are the free tier's: 20 req/minute, and 50 req/day with no
# credits loaded (1,000/day once $10+ has been loaded) -- confirmed
# current 2026-07-07. The full pipeline (Interpretation, Judgment,
# Planner, Response) is 4 calls per conversation turn, so the no-credit
# tier caps out around 12 turns/day; size any recurring automated job
# against that ceiling with real margin for manual/ad hoc calls sharing
# the same key, not right up against it. Set your own model here to pin a
# specific one instead, with the rate-limit caveat above in mind.
OPENROUTER_MODEL=openrouter/free
# OPENROUTER_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1

# --- Instrumentation (src/instrumentation/usage.py) ---
# Off by default -- measurement only, no effect on normal runs. Set to 1
# to record token/cost/latency per LLM call and print a per-turn summary
# from conversation_runner.py / scripts/run_worldstate_walkthrough.py.
# Turn this on for evaluation runs (see
# engine/specs/judgment-v2-evaluation-design.md), leave it off otherwise.
CONFIDANT_TRACK_USAGE=0
